The paper focuses on content-based image retrieval and pattern spotting using deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of pre-trained CNN models and Siamese Convolution Neural Networks also suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.DL) techniques. Additionally, the evaluation of retrieval performance and comparison against state-of-the-art methods suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
